<ol><li>The&nbsp;<b>MAC address</b>&nbsp;is stripped off by the linked layer.</li><li>The&nbsp;<b>IP addresses</b>&nbsp;are removed by the network layer.</li><li>The transport layer use&nbsp;<b>port number</b>&nbsp;to decide which application to pass the data to, and&nbsp;<b>reassembles the packets</b>&nbsp;in the correct order.</li><li>The application layer presents the data for the user.</li></ol>